ğŸš€ STEPS to create the executable
(1) FIRST STEP: Prepare the files
    (i) Create a folder on your computer (e.g., C:\BriCANet\)
    (ii) Save the file BriCANet_GUI.py inside this folder
    (iii) Save the file requirements.txt inside this folder

(2) SECOND STEP: Install everything you need
    (i) Open the Command Prompt (CMD): type cmd and press Enter
    (ii) Navigate to the project folder by typing: cd C:\BriCANet
    (iii) Install the required Python libraries with: pip install -r requirements.txt
    (iv) Install PyInstaller (to create the executable) with: pip install pyinstaller

(3) THIRD STEP: Create the executable
    In the command prompt, run the following command: pyinstaller --onefile --windowed --name="BriCANet_Classifier" --clean --noconsole --hidden-import=tensorflow --hidden-import=pil bricanet_gui.py

Once PyInstaller finishes, BriCANet will be ready to use! ğŸ‰

Your folder structure will look like this:
C:\BriCANet\
